 within which to plot tribal ethnic expressions in the past. From the perspective of the longue durée, we can see that frontier regions tend to exhibit episodic changes of hand: competing sides claimed legitimate ownership, sometimes by way of making the gods owners of the land.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEthnicityxJordan. 0aEthnicityzJordan. 0aEthnoarchaeologyxJordan. 0aEthnoarchaeologyzJordan. 0aIron agexJordan. 0aIron agezJordan. 0aJewsxHistoryx1200-953 B.C. 0aJewsxHistoryy1200-953 B.C. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311074525240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781575068756?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781575068756423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781575068756/original  a978-3-11-074525-2  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK